<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 14 at 8:32AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Snow and Blowing Snow will impact portions Glacier, Toole, and
Pondera Counties this morning...
Periods of snow, occasionally heavy, and northwesterly winds
gusting upwards of 35 mph will impact portions of Glacier, Toole,
and Pondera Counties throughout the morning. Anyone traveling
along US-2 from Inverness to Cut Bank should expect slippery roads
and reduced visibility as low as half a mile at times in snow and
blowing snow. Use caution if you must commute and give yourself
extra time to get to your destination.</description>
